function to search playlist by name¶

In [4]:
def getplaylist(keyword,ignorecase=True, dic=id_playlist_dict,n=[0,10],len_filter=[5,30]):
    '''
    search playlist in id_playlist_dict by keyword
    n: result selection. Selected like a list.
    len_filter: lower bound and upper bound for playlist length
    return : a list of ('playlistname',[songlist])
    '''
    if ignorecase:
        reg = re.compile(keyword,flags=re.IGNORECASE)
    else:
        reg = re.compile(keyword)        
    res =[]
    for key,value in dic.items():
        if reg.findall(key) and len(value)>=len_filter[0] and len(value) <= len_filter[1]:
            res.append((key,value))
    sta,end = n
    if len(res)<end:
        return res[sta:]
    else:
        return res[sta:end]

In [5]:
def plot_cosine(name):
    res = searchsong(song_count=song_count,keyword=name,n=10)
    vec = [m2v.wv.get_vector(item[0]) for item in res]
    df = pd.DataFrame(cosine_similarity(vec),index=[item[0] for item in res])
    df.index.name = "Cosine Similarity"
    df
    plt.figure(figsize=(9,6))
    #sns.set()
    ax = sns.heatmap(df,annot=True,cmap="YlGnBu",)
    ax.tick_params(labelsize=14)
    ax.set_title("Top {} Song's Similarity".format(name),fontsize=20)

plot playlist:¶

draw playlist as series in two-dim embedding space.

Matplotlib¶

In [8]:
def getplaylist_xy(search_res,embedding_df=df_tsne):
    X=[];Y=[];pname = search_res[0];sname=search_res[1]
    for i,j in enumerate(search_res[1]):
        x,y = embedding_df.loc[j,:]
        X.append(x)
        Y.append(y)
    return pname,sname,X,Y

def plotplaylist(res):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6.4))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    plt.xlim(xmin-2,xmax+2)
    plt.ylim(ymin-2,ymax+2)
    plt.scatter(df_tsne['0'],df_tsne['1'],alpha=0.01,label='_nolegend_')
    for i in res:
        pname,sname,x,y = getplaylist_xy(i)
        ax.plot(x, y, 'grey', zorder=1, lw=1)
        ax.scatter(x, y,s=30,alpha=0.8, zorder=2,label=re.split(">>",pname)[1])
        #ax.scatter(x[0],y[0],s=100,zorder=3)
    box = ax.get_position()
    ax.set_position([box.x0, box.y0, box.width * 0.8, box.height])
    # Put a legend to the right of the current axis
    ax.legend(title="Playlist",loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5))
    plt.title("playlist embedding")
    plt.show()
